Label: Grey
Caption: This project showcases the huge diversity in the tree species around the world. From the thick and wet Texas swamps, to the glacial climate of the Canadian subarctic and the dry isolation of Namibia's deserts, this project covers different seasons and totally different subjects. Each tree species has a different impact on the planet and grows differently in its environment, and this is showcased by using a variety of perspectives: wide angle, aerial and telephoto. Trees are not only a stunningly simple photography subject, but are also a symbol of Earth's ecosystem, as well as an indicator of the wider environmental trends.
Title: The Lungs of the Earth
